        <body>
            <div type="letter">
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date when="1924-08-13">
                            <emph rend="underlined">13th Aug. 1924</emph> <lb/>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>                  
                    <salute>
                        Dear <persName key="Q703935">Woolf</persName>, <lb/>
                    </salute>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    &#49; I <unclear reason="bad handwriting" cert="high">refuse</unclear> the agreement duly <lb/>Signed. &#50; We should like either <lb/>P.V. &#48;&#49;&#50; or PVA. &#52;&#53;&#50; for binding. <lb/>&#51; I am most anxious &#45; <lb/>suppose needlessly anxious &#45; that Major <unclear reason="bad handwriting" cert="medium">Church</unclear> &#40;Lnb. M.P.&#41; and Mr. Linfield <lb/>should have read the <del rend="strikethrough">facts in my</del> &#40;Lnb. M.P.&#41; <lb/>statements in my book <emph rend="underscored">before</emph> they <lb/><del rend="strikethrough"><unclear reason="bad handwriting" cert="low">all</unclear>into</del>land in <placeName>Africa</placeName> <unclear reason="bad handwriting" cert="unknown"></unclear> be led<lb/>about with blinkers on them. Can <lb/><pb/>you as Secretary of the advisory <lb/>Commitee invest your advice <unclear reason="bad handwriting" cert="unknown"></unclear> read <lb/> the book with so great authority <lb/>and <unclear reason="bad handwriting" cert="unknown"></unclear> that it will be <lb/> done&#63; &#52; I hope that by this time <lb/>you have got another letter of mine <lb/>from my brother. <lb/>&#53; Can you lend me a pamphlet <lb/>with instructions on proofcorrecting? Or <lb/>does <unclear reason="bad handwriting" cert="unknown"></unclear> have his own code? If <lb/>so would Clark send me his and will you <lb/>ask him to?
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed/><emph rend="underlined">N Leys</emph> <lb/>
                </closer>
            </div>
